Figure 2 Overall Use Case in System provides an overview of the Use Case Diagram of the FCTF - Version 4 system, showing the main actors and the functions they can interact with in the system. Basic authentication functions such as login and logout are not presented in this diagram, as these are minimal use cases present in almost all systems. The system includes four main roles: Admin, Challenge Writer, Contestant, and Jury. Challenge Writer is responsible for creating, editing, and managing challenges in the system. They can add new, update content, configure, and ensure the quality of challenges. Admin is the role with the highest authority in the system, including all functions of Challenge Writer and Jury, while having extended rights such as user management, team management, and system configuration. Admin is responsible for monitoring all platform activities and ensuring stable system operation. Contestant is the competitor. They can view the challenge list, start or stop the competition environment, submit flags, send support tickets, and track the scoreboard. Jury acts as an observer and evaluator of the contest. Jury has the right to monitor the scoreboard, competition progress, submission information, and respond to support tickets to ensure fairness and transparency. 
