Figure 9: Screen Flow of Management System
Figure 9 describes the FCTF management system, which is designed with a central interface being the Admin Dashboard, allowing administrators (admin), juries, and challenge writers to effectively manage, monitor, and operate all system activities. Through this interface, administrators can quickly access important functions such as Dashboard, Challenges, Users, Action Logs, Tickets, Teams, Scoreboard, Submissions, Dynamic Reward Query, Config, Monitoring, Instances History, and Audit Log.
The Dashboard page provides an overview of the system's operational status, including statistics related to the number of users, participating teams, challenges, submissions, and necessary reporting information. The Challenges function supports managing the entire lifecycle of challenges, from creating new ones, editing content, and configuring difficulty, to tracking deployment status and activity history. Through the Users and Teams sections, administrators can manage account information, assign permissions, track user activity status, as well as organize and coordinate participating teams.
The Action Logs system is used to record all contestant activities during their participation in the contest, including accessing the system, submitting answers, deploying instances, and related information. This data supports tracking the competition progress and detecting abnormal behaviors when necessary. In addition, the Submissions function allows administrators to monitor the flag submission process, check results, and analyze submission data to ensure fairness and transparency.
The Tickets function serves as the official support channel between contestants and the organizers, helping to receive, process, and respond to requests in a timely manner. The Scoreboard page displays and manages the leaderboard, accurately reflecting the rankings and scores of teams throughout the duration of the contest. Furthermore, the system integrates the Dynamic Reward Query function to support the analysis and extraction of information for the purpose of awarding prizes based on the established criteria.
The Config section allows administrators to set up and adjust system configuration parameters, including security policies, resource management, and operational options. The Monitoring function supports tracking the status of currently deployed challenge instances, helping to monitor these challenge instances and detect technical issues early. Besides that, Instances History stores the complete history of deploying, initializing, stopping, and destroying challenge instances, supporting effective inspection and resource management.
In addition to tracking contestant activities through Action Logs, the system also provides an Audit Log function specifically for administrators, aimed at recording all actions affecting the system at the administrative level, including configuration changes, data edits, challenge updates, and other important management operations. This function contributes to enhancing transparency, supporting auditing and traceability, and ensuring safety during system operation.
Overall, the FCTF management system is organized in a clear, scientific, and intuitive functional structure, making it easy for administrators to control all activities of the contest, while ensuring the system operates stably, safely, and effectively.
