4.3.5. Rancher
Rancher operates as a management layer on top of the Kubernetes API Server. It provides a web UI, API proxy, and centralized multi-cluster management capabilities.
•	Trust Boundary: The boundary lies between the Management Zone (Rancher) and the Control Plane Zone (Kubernetes API). Rancher holds ServiceAccounts or Kubeconfigs with cluster-admin privileges. 
•	Risk Level: Critical. Rancher represents a single point of failure for cluster management. If Rancher is compromised, all security policies, network policies, and workloads within the cluster can potentially be disabled or bypassed.
