4.3.6. Redis Analysis
Redis is a high-performance, in-memory store that supports both operational efficiency and security for the challenge platform. Its key functions include:
•	Rate Limiting at Challenge Gateway: Tracks requests per IP/token/global with TTL counters and atomic Lua scripts, enforcing allow/deny decisions to prevent abuse. 
•	Challenge Deployment State Sync (.NET Services): Manages active deployments via ZSETs, storing reservations and TTLs. Supports cleanup of expired instances and prevents race conditions. 
•	Authentication Caching & Brute-force Protection: Caches tokens, tracks submission attempts with cooldowns, and blocks brute-force or spam in real-time. 
•	Admin MVC (CTFd) Caching & Orchestration: Provides application-level caching to improve responsiveness and scalability of administrative operations. 
Redis centralizes ephemeral state and control logic, ensuring both performance and system integrity across distributed services.
